<body>

<main class="edu-wrapper">

  <div class="edu-kicker">
    EDUCATION & WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT
  </div>

  <h1 class="edu-title">
    Training the Next Generation of <span>Multi-Omics Scientists</span>
  </h1>

  <p class="edu-intro">
    The PanorOmics Omics Sciences Center is a United States–based biotechnology
    organization dedicated to advancing omics sciences education, workforce
    development, and translational scientific discovery.
  </p>

  <section class="edu-section">
    <h2>Our Mission</h2>
    <p>
      Our mission is to help train the next generation of multi-omics scientists
      who will contribute to closing critical workforce gaps in biotechnology,
      pharmaceutical sciences, healthcare innovation, and academic research.
      We believe the future of biomedical discovery depends on scientists who
      can integrate genomics, transcriptomics, epigenomics, proteomics,
      metabolomics, lipidomics, computational biology, artificial intelligence,
      and translational biotechnology into a unified scientific framework.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="edu-section">
    <h2>Why Omics Sciences Education Matters</h2>
    <p>
      Modern biology is becoming increasingly data-rich, computational, and
      interdisciplinary. Omics sciences provide the foundation for understanding
      biological systems at scale, while computational biology and artificial
      intelligence help researchers interpret complex molecular data and
      translate discovery into real-world biomedical impact.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="edu-section">
    <h2>The Door Is Open</h2>
    <p>
      PanorOmics was built for learners who are seeking a pathway into modern
      life sciences. Scientific opportunity should be accessible, rigorous,
      and globally relevant. We aim to support students, researchers,
      healthcare professionals, biotechnology teams, and lifelong learners
      who want to participate in the future of biological discovery.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="edu-highlight">
    <h2>PanED: Boundless Education</h2>
    <p>
      To expand access to modern omics sciences education, PanorOmics connects
      learners to PanED, an independent educational platform designed to provide
      accessible, high-quality learning experiences for learners worldwide.
      PanED supports Omics Sciences 101 courses, digital badges, professional
      development, and future workforce training initiatives for biotechnology,
      healthcare, pharmaceutical sciences, and academic research.
    </p>

    <a href="https://paned.org" class="edu-button">
      Launch PanED &rarr;
    </a>
  </section>

  <div class="edu-footer">
    PanorOmics © 2026 • Pittsburgh, PA • USA
  </div>

